d NSSC as the dissolving company, effective as of April 1, 2025.", "score": 0.7460839, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://www.findlaw.com/legalblogs/courtside/the-iron-price-u-s-steel-and-nippon-steel-sue-after-their-merger-is-blocked", "title": "The Iron Price \\u2014 U.S. Steel and Nippon Steel Sue After Their Merger Is Blocked", "content": "The ensuing CFIUS review could not reach a consensus on whether or not the deal threatened national security. This non-committal allowed Biden to exercise the executive authority to suspend or prohibit a foreign investment deemed a threat to national security. After Biden nixed the deal on January 3rd, 2025, the companies quickly responded by filing lawsuits in federal court.", "score": 0.68874115, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://www.mesabitribune.com/news/u-s-steel-nippon-steel-merger-would-secure-mon-valley-works/article_2af2d7b6-80ce-11ef-b34d-678e40c60e9d.html", "title": "U.S. Steel: Nippon Steel merger would secure Mon Valley Works | News | mesabitribune.com", "content": "Without a merger of the two steel companies, U.S. Steel has said it will largely pivot away from its blast furnace facilities.\\n\\nThat would put thousands of good-paying union jobs at risk, according to U.S. Steel.\\n\\nThe company\\u2019s blast furnaces are fed by iron ore pellets produced at its Minnesota Ore Operations facilities at Minntac Mine in Mountain Iron and Keetac in Keewatin.\\n\\nWithout closure of the deal, U.S. Steel\\u2019s headquarters in Pittsburgh could also be moved, the company said.", "score": 0.66229486, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://khabarasia.com/business/20250106-nippon-steel-and-u-s-steel-sue-biden-administration-over-blocked-merger", "title": "Nippon Steel and U.S. Steel Sue Biden Administration Over Blocked Merger - Khabar Asia", "content": "The proposed acquisition, which would see Nippon Steel integrate U.S. Steel into its operations, has faced opposition from the U.S. government. The companies argue 