ain unchanged.\\u201d. He added: \\u201cWhile we await the details of the proposed investment, we encourage President Trump to continue safeguarding the long-term future of the domestic steel industry by instead seeking American alternatives.\\u201d. Mr. Trump said on Friday that he remained opposed to Nippon\\u2019s owning the company but that an investment was \\u201cvery", "score": 0.694241, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://stratnewsglobal.com/world-news/nippon-steel-considers-shift-in-u-s-steel-acquisition-strategy", "title": "Nippon Steel Considers Shift In U.S. Steel Acquisition Strategy", "content": "On Friday, U.S. President Donald Trump said Nippon Steel\\u2019s $14.9 billion bid for U.S. Steel would take the form of an investment instead of a purchase. Two people familiar with the matter said the biggest Japanese steelmaker had not withdrawn its bid.\\n\\nNippon Steel declined to comment on Hayashi\\u2019s comment as well as Trump\\u2019s latest statement that no one can have a majority stake in U.S. Steel.", "score": 0.6659544, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://steelindustry.news/trump-announces-nippon-steels-strategic-investment-in-u-s-steel", "title": "Trump Announces Nippon Steel\'s Strategic Investment in U.S. Steel", "content": "on protecting and strengthening American industry. Trump\\u2019s announcement of Nippon Steel\\u2019s planned investment in U.S. Steel marks a pivotal moment in the American steel industry. It represents a compromise that aims to preserve U.S. Steel\\u2019s American identity while leveraging international expertise and capital123.As the details of this investment unfold in the coming weeks, all eyes will be on how this partnership develops and its potential to revitalize one of America\\u2019s most iconic industries.", "score": 0.64719695, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://www.marketbeat.com/originals/us-steel-will-trump-backed-nippon-investment-drive-upside", "title": "U.S. Steel Stock: More Upside After Trump Supports Nippon Deal?", "content": "However, in early January 2025, President Joe Biden, through the Committee on Foreign Investment in the United States (CFIUS), blocked the deal, citing national security concerns as the justification. This was an unusual decision. It is the only time that CFIUS has prevented a transaction without Chinese ownership or influence ties. U.S. Steel and Nippon have filed multiple lawsuits against this decision. If they win these lawsuits, the deal could go through.", "score": 0.51457167, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://www.uppermichiganssource.com/2025/01/03/biden-rejects-nippon-steel-proposal-acquire-us-steel", "title": "Biden rejects Nippon Steel proposal to acquire US Steel", "content": "Goncalves said the Trump administration had also identified security risks associated with the deal, saying then-Senators J.D. Vance, Marco Rubio and Josh Hawley requested CFIUS block the sale of U.S. Steel to Nippon Steel following its announced proposal. He said the then-senators followed up with a letter to President Biden on May 9, 2024, urging him to reject it.", "score": 0.45769477, "raw_content": null}]',
